insect.coverage.analysis.jaba
Class JABAExecCoverage

java.lang.Object
  insect.coverage.analysis.jaba.JABAExecCoverage
public class JABAExecCoverage
extends java.lang.Object

Computes coverage information for entities in a JABA GDG graph by mapping its information to the InsECT interface. This class is actually backed by the ExecCoverage class.

Author:
Anil Chawla

wasEdgeCovered

public java.lang.Boolean wasEdgeCovered(jaba.graph.Edge edge)
Determines if the specified generic statement-to-statement edge was covered. If the source statement is a predicate, branch coverage is taken into account. Otherwise, it is assumed that the edge is covered if both source and sink nodes are.

Parameters:
edge - statement-to-statement edge
Returns:
a Boolean specifying true or false, or null on error
